Effective Date: 07/01/2023



This Privacy Policy describes how (https://www.edgesmartchain.com/EdgeSmart, we", "Edge" or "our") collects, uses, stores, shares and protects your personal information when you participate in, download, view or use our website (including without limitation the website, edgesmartchain.com, the "Site"), any of our services, including but not limited to the EdgeSmart Services or any mobile application we offer, any page, feature or website provided or sponsored by EdgeSmart Content, any of our application programming interfaces (“APIs”), or any third-party applications that rely on such APIs (collectively, the “Services”). By downloading, using, or participating in the Services, you agree to the data practices set forth in this Privacy Policy. As described below, EdgeSmart may periodically change this Privacy Policy. It is your responsibility to review this Privacy Policy frequently, and EdgeSmart encourages you to visit this page frequently. By accessing and using our Services, you accept the terms of this Privacy Policy and agree to the collection, use, and disclosure of your personal information as described below. If you do not agree to this Privacy Policy or are uncomfortable with any aspect of this Privacy Policy, you should immediately stop accessing or using our Services. Please take a moment to read this Privacy Policy carefully. If you have any questions about this Policy, please contact us at https://www.edgesmartchain.com/ and If EdgeSmart requires your consent to process your Personal Information, EdgeSmart will ask for your consent to collect, use and disclose your Personal Information as described below. EdgeSmart may provide additional " Immediately” disclosures or information. These statements may supplement or clarify our privacy practices, or may provide you with additional choices about how EdgeSmart handles your data.



Changes to this Privacy Policy EdgeSmart may revise this Privacy Policy from time to time, which will be indicated by changing the date at the top of this page. If EdgeSmart makes any material changes, EdgeSmart will notify you by email (sent to the email address specified in your account), via our service notifications before the changes become effective, or as otherwise required by law. EdgeSmart operates entities (collectively "EdgeSmart", "Edge", "we" and "our") around the world to provide services to our customers. When you communicate with any EdgeSmart, you may be asked to provide personal information. EdgeSmart may share your personal information with each other and use it in accordance with this Privacy Policy. We may also combine it with other information to provide and improve our products, services and content (further details below). For example, even if you do not reside in the United States (“United States”), your information may be shared with Metal Financial Services, Inc. (United States), which provides global support for all services, including technical infrastructure, product development, security, compliance, fraud prevention, and customer support.



Collection of Information Information You Provide to Us EdgeSmart collects personal information that you provide to us directly or indirectly. This includes information you provide to us, information collected about you automatically, and information EdgeSmart obtains from third parties. "Personal Information" means information about you that personally identifies you or that identifies you, which can be identified with other information such as your name, address, email address or telephone number. Personal information does not include de-identified, aggregated, or information that cannot be reasonably linked to an identifiable individual. For example, EdgeSmart collects your personal information when you create a registered account to use one of our services, download or use our mobile applications, complete transactions on our websites or mobile applications, fill out forms through our websites or mobile applications, respond to our surveys, enter sweepstakes, contests or other promotions offered to you by EdgeSmart, post messages on our forums, or otherwise communicate with us. The types of personal information that EdgeSmart collects vary depending on the Services you access, participate in, or use. The types of personal information that EdgeSmart may collect are as follows:



  • Personally identifiable information such as your full name, mailing address, telephone number, date of birth, nationality, gender, signature, email address.



• Financial information, such as virtual currency account information, transaction history, transaction data and/or tax identification.



• A government identification number, such as your social security number or state-issued identification number. Government-issued identification such as passports, driver’s licenses, national ID cards, state ID cards, tax file numbers, passport numbers, driver’s license details, national ID card details, visa details and/or any other information necessary to comply with our legal obligations under financial or anti-money laundering laws.



• Personal or demographic information, such as your date of birth, gender, occupation, employment status and any other personal information about yourself that you choose to provide.



• Transaction Information: Information about transactions you make on our Services, such as the recipient's name, your name, amount and/or timestamp.



• Employment Information: Office location, job title and/or role description.



• Communications: survey responses, information provided to our support team or user research team.



Information EdgeSmart Collects from Other Sources EdgeSmart may also obtain information from other sources as permitted or required by law and combine it with Personal Information that EdgeSmart collects through the Services. For example, EdgeSmart may collect nonpublic personal information about you from third parties, including identity verification services. EdgeSmart obtains financial transaction history (including user's bank account or credit card account transaction history) through suppliers as necessary to perform certain services and to verify your identity in accordance with applicable law. Such information may include your name, address, job role, public employment profile, credit history, status on any sanctions lists maintained by public authorities, and other relevant data. EdgeSmart obtains this information in order to comply with our legal obligations, such as anti-money laundering laws. In some cases, EdgeSmart may process other data about you to ensure that our services are not being used for fraudulent or other illegal activities. In such cases, processing is necessary for our continued performance of our contractual obligations with you and others.



• Blockchain data: EdgeSmartChain may analyze public blockchain data to ensure that parties using our services are not engaging in illegal or prohibited activities in accordance with our terms, and to analyze transaction trends for research and development purposes.



• Joint Marketing Partners and Resellers: For example, unless prohibited by applicable law, joint marketing partners or resellers may share information about you with us so that EdgeSmart can better understand which services may be of interest to you.



• Ad networks and analytics providers: EdgeSmart works with these providers to provide us with de-identified information about how you found our site and how you interacted with the site and services. This information may be collected prior to account creation - see the Cookie Policy below for more information on how to manage the collection of this data.



Information EdgeSmart Automatically Collects EdgeSmart automatically receives and stores certain types of information, such as when you interact with the Site or use the Services. This information helps us resolve customer support issues, improve the performance of our websites and applications, provide you with a simplified and personalized experience, and prevent fraud by detecting unauthorized access. Information that is automatically collected includes: EdgeSmart automatically collects personal information when you download, access or use the Services, as follows:



• Transaction Information: EdgeSmart collects information about transactions you complete through the Services.



• Location Information: EdgeSmart may collect precise geolocation/tracking information from your mobile device when you visit or use our mobile applications or other websites (including at national and state levels). EdgeSmart will also collect your personal IP address, browser fingerprint browser name and version, and operating system. EdgeSmart also collects user location information when you visit certain services on our website (for example, or our EdgeSmart service).



• Device and Log Information: EdgeSmart collects information about the computer or mobile device you use in connection with the Services, including device type and identifier, mobile network information, type of operating system, and type of browser used. EdgeSmart also logs information about your use of the Services, including time of visit, pages viewed, IP address, other standard web log data, and pages visited before and after navigating to our site. This may include authentication data, security questions, clickstream data, public social network posts, and other data collected through cookies and similar technologies. see below. Device event information (such as crashes, system activity and hardware settings, browser type, browser language, date and time of request, and referring URL); how your device interacts with our Site and Services, including pages visited and links clicked.



COOKIES AND LOCAL STORAGE EdgeSmart may use cookies, pixel tags, web beacons, and other tracking technologies to collect information about your interactions with the Services, including information about your browsing or navigation behavior on the Services. A cookie is a small data file sent from our web server to your computer or mobile device, for example, to enable us to capture how you arrived at the Services, when you returned, which pages or features on the Services you used or accessed, and to recognize that you are logged in when EdgeSmart receives a page request from your browser. You can modify your browser settings to refuse cookies or to notify you when a cookie is set. However, if you choose to decline cookies, you may not be able to use some interactive features of our website. You can go back and delete cookies from your browser at any time, however, this means that any settings or preferences controlled by those cookies will also be deleted and you may need to re-create them. See www.allaboutcookies.org for more information. EdgeSmart may use industry-wide technologies, such as "cookies" or similar technologies, that store certain information on your computer ("local storage") when you access or use the Services, which will enable us to enable automatic activation of certain features and make your experience with our Services more convenient and easy. Cookies used by the Services are created on a per-session basis and contain no information about you other than your session key (which is deleted at the end of your session (usually after 24 hours)) and the ability to quickly log in again (usually automatically deleted after two years unless manually deleted earlier). Disabling local storage is easy. Most browsers allow you to delete cookies from your computer's hard drive, block the acceptance of cookies or receive a warning before storing a cookie. However, if you block or delete cookies, your online experience may be limited. In addition to the standard cookies mentioned above, please note that EdgeSmart may also use electronic tags, which will allow us to recognize user behavior. We can only delete such electronic tags upon receipt of your written request in this regard. EdgeSmart may also use certain third-party cookies. This is a different type of cookie and is stored on your computer by a third party rather than us. These cookies are read-only (we will not change them) each time you use the Services and visit certain websites or applications that use similar cookies.



Anonymizing and Aggregating Data Anonymization is a data processing technique that removes or modifies personal information so that it cannot be associated with a specific individual. Except for this section, nothing else in this Privacy Policy applies to anonymized or aggregated customer data (that is, information about our customers that EdgeSmart has combined so that individual customers are no longer identified or referenced). EdgeSmart may use anonymized or aggregated customer data for any business purpose, including better understanding customer needs and behavior, improving our products and services, business intelligence and marketing, and detecting security threats. EdgeSmart may perform our own analysis or enable analysis provided by third parties on the anonymous data. The types of data that EdgeSmart may anonymize include transactional data, clickstream data, performance metrics, and fraud indicators.



