tion to administer our legal, regulatory, financial and business requirements, including obtaining legal advice during disputes and litigation, internal and/or regulatory investigations. For our business purposes: EdgeSmart may use your personal information to help us efficiently operate the Services, count and identify visitors to our Services, enable certain features on or within our Services, and for other purposes related to administering our business EdgeSmart processes sensitive information, such as your identity and financial data, so it is important to us and our customers that EdgeSmart actively monitors, investigates, prevents, and mitigates any potentially prohibited or illegal activity, enforces our agreements with third parties, and/or prevents and detects Violation of our posted user agreement or other service agreements. In addition, EdgeSmart may require you to charge fees based on your usage of our services. EdgeSmart collects information about your account usage and closely monitors your interactions with our Services. EdgeSmart may use any personal information collected from you for these purposes. Failure to process your personal information for such purposes will result in termination of your account. For example, when you want to store cryptocurrency on our platform, EdgeSmart requires certain information, such as your identity, contact information and payment information. Without such information, EdgeSmart will not be able to provide services to you. For fraud protection and detection: EdgeSmart processes your personal information to help detect, prevent and mitigate fraud and abuse of our services, and to protect you from account compromise or loss of funds related to such fraud. To communicate with our consumers: EdgeSmart sends you administrative or account-related messages to keep you informed about our services, notify you of relevant security issues or updates, or provide other transaction-related information. Without such communications, you may not be aware of important developments related to your account that may affect how you use our Services. You may not opt-out of receiving service-critical communications, such as email or mobile notifications for legal or security purposes. To provide customer support: EdgeSmart processes your personal information when you contact us with any questions, disputes, billing or resolution. Without processing your personal information for such purposes, EdgeSmart will be unable to answer your support questions and ensure your uninterrupted use of the services. For quality control: EdgeSmart processes your personal information for quality control and staff training purposes to ensure that EdgeSmart continues to provide you with accurate information. If EdgeSmart does not process personal information for quality control purposes, you may experience problems with the service, such as inaccurate transaction recording or other interruptions. For online security: EdgeSmart processes your personal information to enhance security, monitor and verify identity or service access, combat spam or other malware or security risks, and comply with applicable security laws and regulations. The ever-evolving threat landscape on the Internet makes it more important than ever for EdgeSmart to have accurate and up-to-date information about your use of our services. EdgeSmart may not be able to ensure the security of our services without processing your personal information. For research and development: EdgeSmart processes your personal information to better understand how you use and interact with the Metal X Services. In addition, EdgeSmart uses such information to customize, measure and improve EdgeSmart's services and the content and layout of our websites and applications, and to develop new services. Without such processing, EdgeSmart cannot ensure your continued enjoyment of our services. Improving the Consumer Experience EdgeSmart processes your personal information to provide a personalized experience and enforce your requested preferences. For example, you may choose to provide us with access to certain personal information stored by third parties. Without such processing, EdgeSmart may not be able to ensure your continued enjoyment of some or all of our services. In the event of a corporate acquisition, merger or transaction EdgeSmart may process any information about your account and use of our Services in the event of a corporate acquisition, merger or other corporate transaction. If you do not wish your personal information to be processed for such purposes, you may choose to close your account. Promotional Marketing Depending on your communication preferences, EdgeSmart may send you marketing communications (such as email or mobile notifications) to inform you of our events or our partners' events; to provide targeted marketing; and to provide you with promotional offers. Our marketing will be based on your demonstrated marketing preferences where permitted by applicable law. Direct Marketing: Direct marketing includes any communications sent to you solely to advertise or promote our products and services. EdgeSmart will only contact you electronically (email or SMS) based on our legitimate interests, as permitted by applicable law or with your consent. To the extent EdgeSmart may rely on a legitimate interest under applicable law, EdgeSmart will only send you information about our Services that is similar to the subject of a previous sale to you or negotiation of a sale. If you are a new customer, EdgeSmart will contact you electronically for marketing purposes only if you consent to such communications. If you do not want us to send you marketing communications, please submit a written request to opt-out via https://www.edgesmartchain.com/ You may raise such an objection at any time regarding initial or further processing for direct marketing purposes free of charge. Direct marketing includes any communication with you solely on the basis of advertising or promoting our products and services. Third Party Marketing: EdgeSmart will obtain your express consent before EdgeSmart will share your personal information with any third party for marketing purposes. For any other purpose EdgeSmart may use your personal information for other purposes in connection with the Services, subject to your prior consent, in accordance with applicable law.



