Why EdgeSmart Shares Personal Information with Other Parties EdgeSmart takes care to only allow access to your Personal Information to those who need access to perform their tasks and responsibilities, and only shares it with third parties who have legitimate access purposes. EdgeSmart will never send yoursell or rent personal information to third parties. EdgeSmart will only share your information in the following circumstances: Use third-party authentication services to prevent fraud. This enables EdgeSmart to confirm your identity by comparing the information you provide us with public records and other third-party databases. These service providers may create derived data based on your personal information, which may only be used to provide identity verification and fraud prevention services. EdgeSmart will not sell or rent any of your personal information to third parties for their own marketing purposes. Please be aware that third parties who support our customer identification and anti-fraud controls may retain and use your personal information to perform and improve their services on our behalf. By using any of the Services, you consent to these providers retaining and using such information to improve their services. EdgeSmart may also share aggregated or de-identified information with our affiliates or unaffiliated third parties that cannot reasonably be used to identify you. Personal information that EdgeSmart collects from you may be transferred to and stored at destinations outside your country of residence. EdgeSmart uses reasonable technical and organizational security measures to protect your personal information when it is transferred or shared with us or our affiliates or our third party recipients.



Information Protection Although no data processing and transmission can be guaranteed to be 100% secure, EdgeSmart takes reasonable steps to protect all personal information. EdgeSmart uses industry standard encryption technology to protect the account registration process and registration information. Additional security safeguards include, but are not limited to, data encryption, firewalls, and physical access controls to buildings and files. EdgeSmart understands the importance of your privacy, which is why EdgeSmart maintains (and third parties with whom you are contractually required to share your information with) appropriate physical, technical and administrative safeguards to protect the security and confidentiality of the personal information you entrust to us. EdgeSmart may store and process all or some of your personal and transactional information, including certain payment information such as your encrypted bank account and/or routing numbers, in the United States and elsewhere in the world where our facilities or service providers are located. EdgeSmart protects your personal information by maintaining physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards that comply with applicable laws and regulations. For example, EdgeSmart uses computer protection measures such as firewalls and data encryption, EdgeSmart implements physical access controls to our buildings and files, and EdgeSmart authorizes access to personal information only to those employees who need it to perform their job duties. However, EdgeSmart cannot guarantee against loss, misuse, unauthorized access or alteration of your data. Please recognize that you play a vital role in protecting your personal information. When registering with our services, it is important to choose a password of sufficient length and complexity, not to disclose this password to any third party, and to notify us immediately if you become aware of any unauthorized access to or use of your account. In addition, EdgeSmart cannot ensure or warrant the security or confidentiality of information you transmit to or receive from us over the Internet or wireless connections (including email, phone calls, or text messages), because EdgeSmart cannot protect that information once it leaves and reaches us. If you have reason to believe that your data is no longer secure, please contact us using the contact information provided in this Privacy Policy.



Deletion of Personal Information If for any reason you wish to delete your personal information stored with us, please email us at: https://www.edgesmartchain.com/ and EdgeSmart will use reasonable efforts to delete any such personal information in accordance with any applicable privacy laws and consistent with reasonable record keeping practices. EdgeSmartt may need to retain certain personal information for business records purposes, tax or other legal requirements, or other purposes permitted by applicable data privacy laws. EdgeSmart may need to request information from you to verify your identity before accepting a deletion request. EdgeSmart will retain your personal information for at least five years or as necessary to comply with our legal obligations or to resolve disputes. EdgeSmart will also retain copies of your information to the extent retained as part of our standard backup/archive process. In addition, these programs do not delete any information you have provided to other users or third parties, or that third parties have collected from websites or services linked to our Services.



Retention of Personal Information EdgeSmart securely stores your personal information throughout the life of your EdgeSmart account. EdgeSmart will only retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which EdgeSmart collected the information, including to comply with any legal, accounting or reporting obligations or to resolve disputes. While retention requirements vary by jurisdiction, the following describes our typical retention periods for different aspects of your personal information. • Personal information collected to comply with our legal obligations under financial or anti-money laundering laws may be retained after account closure for as long as such laws require. • Contact information for marketing purposes (such as your name, email address and phone number) will remain until you unsubscribe. EdgeSmart will then add your details to our ban list to ensure EdgeSmart does not market to you unintentionally. • Content you post on our site, such as support desk reviews, photos, videos, blog posts and other content, may be retained after you close your account for auditing and crime prevention purposes (for example, to prevent known fraudsters from opening new accounts). • Information collected through technical means such as cookies, web counters and other analytical tools will be retained for up to one year after the cookie expires.



Access and object to processing Under applicable data privacy laws, you may have the right to request access to your personal information or to object to processing or to request that personal information you have provided to us be sent to another organisation. If you wish to exercise these legal rights, please contact us at https://www.edgesmartchain.com/ and EdgeSmart will require sufficient information to establish your identity and the nature of your request. EdgeSmart aims to respond to your request within one calendar month of receipt. If EdgeSmart is unable to do so within the calendar month, EdgeSmart will notify you of the fastest practicable time when EdgeSmart can respond to your request. EdgeSmart will notify you of these rights, subject to applicable data privacy laws, with certain exemptions and limitations that allow retention, processing or denial of access to personal information.



California Privacy Rights California law permits customers who are California residents to request certain information regarding our disclosure of personal information to third parties during the previous calendar year for their own direct marketing purposes. However, EdgeSmart will not sell or rent your personal information to any third parties for their own marketing. For questions, please contact us at https://www.edgesmartchain.com/ Pursuant to the California Consumer Privacy Act of 12 (“CCPA”), California residents have certain rights regarding their personal information, subject to limited exceptions. Any terms defined in the CCPA have the same meaning when used in this California Privacy Rights Section. You can do this by visiting https://www.edgesmartchain.com/ and California residents have the right to request information about whether EdgeSmart shares certain categories of personal information with third parties for their direct marketing purposes. If EdgeSmartn shares your personal information in this way, you may receive certain messages as follows:



• (a) the categories of information that EdgeSmart has disclosed to third parties for the third party's direct marketing purposes during the preceding calendar year;



• (b) the name and address of the third party to whom such information was received, or if the nature of its business cannot be ascertained from the name, an example of the product or service being sold. • California residents have the right to access and delete personal information that we have collected within the past 40 months, subject to no other exceptions. EdgeSmart does not discriminate against persons exercising their rights. Specifically, EdgeSmart will not deny you service, charge you a different price for service, or provide you with a different level or quality of service if you exercise your rights. • If EdgeSmart sells your personal information to third parties, you also have the right to request that EdgeSmart disclose to you: (i) the categories of your personal information that EdgeSmart sold, and (ii) the categories of third parties to whom your personal information was sold. You have the right to instruct us not to sell your personal information. EdgeSmart does not sell your personal information in the normal course of its business, and will never sell your personal information to third parties without your express consent. If EdgeSmart engages in any of the activities listed in this section, you will obtain your ability to exercise these rights by contacting us at https://www.edgesmartchain.com/ so that edgesmartchain.com can consider your request. If you are a California resident, you may designate an authorized agent to make access requests or deletion requests on your behalf. edgesmartchain.com will respond to your authorized attorney's request if edgesmartchain.com submits proof that they are registered with the California Secretary of State to act on your behalf or submits evidence of a power of attorney you provided to them pursuant to California Probate Code Sections 4465 to <>. edgesmartchain.com may deny requests for authorized agents who do not submit proof that you are authorized to act on their behalf or cannot verify their identity.



