Data transferred from the European Union under the EU-US Privacy Shield to Metal Financial Services and Metal Financial Services (Estonia) EdgeSmart is committed to subjecting all personal information received from European Union (EU) member states to the applicable principles of the Privacy Shield Framework. To learn more about the Privacy Shield framework, visit the U.S. Department of Commerce's Privacy Shield listing at https://www.privacyshield.gov. Metal Financial Services, OU, Estonia (“EdgeSmart”), with its principal place of business at Harju maakond, Tallinn, Lasnamae Iinnaosa, Peterburi tee 47. 11415 is responsible for processing personal information it receives under the Privacy Shield framework and subsequently transfers to third parties acting on its behalf. Before EdgeSmart shares your information with any third party not certified under the EU-US Privacy Shield Frameworks, Estonia Metal Financial Services, OU (“EdgeSmart”) will enter into a written agreement requiring the third party to provide at least the same level of privacy protection as those required by those Frameworks and to ensure the same level of protection for personal information as required by applicable data protection laws. European data subjects with questions or complaints about our Privacy Shield certification should first contact EdgeSmart at https://www.edgesmartchain.com/. If EdgeSmart is unable to resolve your complaint or dispute, you may submit your complaint to our designated independent dispute resolution mechanism, the International Center for Dispute Resolution (“ICDR”) operated by the American Arbitration Association (“AAA”). For more information and to file a complaint, you may contact the International Center for Dispute Resolution at +1.212.484.4181 or visit https://go.adr.org/privacyshield.html. If your Privacy Shield complaint cannot be resolved through the channels described above, you may, under certain circumstances, initiate binding arbitration for certain remaining claims that cannot be resolved by other redress mechanisms. See Privacy Shield Attachment 1 at https://www.privacyshield.gov/article?id=ANNEX-I-ntroduction.



