(b) when granting access would adversely affect the privacy of others;



(c) protect our rights and property;



(d) the request is frivolous or vexatious, or for any other reason. • Accessibility and portability. You may ask EdgeSmart to provide you with a copy of the personal information we hold about you. This information will be provided without undue delay, but fees associated with the collection of the information may be charged (where permitted by law), unless such provision adversely affects the rights and freedoms of others. In certain circumstances, you may request to receive your personal information in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format and request that we transfer your personal information directly to another data controller. • Correct incomplete or inaccurate personal information. You may ask us to correct or update any inaccurate personal information about you that EdgeSmart holds. You can do this at any time by logging into your account. • Erase. You may request deletion of your personal information in accordance with applicable law. If you close your EdgeSmart account, EdgeSmart will mark your account in our database as "closed," but will retain certain account information in our database, including your deletion request, as described above. This is necessary to deter fraud, by ensuring that those attempting to commit fraud cannot avoid detection by simply closing their account and opening a new one, and to comply with EdgeSmart's compliance and legal obligations. However, if you close your account, we will not use your personal information for any other purpose and will not share it with third parties except as necessary to prevent fraud and assist law enforcement, legal or regulatory authorities, or in accordance with this Privacy Policy. • Withdrawal of consent. If the processing of your personal information is based on your consent, you may withdraw your consent at any time. Your withdrawal will not affect the lawfulness of processing by EdgeSmart based on consent prior to your withdrawal. • Restriction of processing. In some jurisdictions, applicable law may give you the right to restrict or object to our processing of your personal information in certain circumstances. EdgeSmart may continue to process your personal information if necessary for the defense of legal claims or in any other exceptions permitted by applicable law. • Automated individual decision-making, including profiling. EdgeSmart relies on automated tools to help determine whether a transaction or customer account presents fraud or legal risk. In some jurisdictions, you have the right not to be bound by a decision based solely on the automated processing (including profiling) of your personal information which has a legal or similarly significant effect on you, subject to applicable exceptions under relevant data protection laws.



